India’s Bond Trading Extended Till 6 P.M. Today, Two Traders Say

-- B y   J e a n e t t e   R o d r i g u e s
-- 
2011-09-28T12:14:05Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-28/india-s-bond-trading-extended-till-6-p-m-today-two-traders-say.html
Trading in  India ’s government bonds
have been extended by an hour to 6 p.m. local time today,
according to a message flashed on the central bank’s trading
system, said two traders, including Anoop Verma, a fixed-income
trader at Development Credit Bank in Mumbai.  To contact the reporter on this story:
